This article is a letter from President Barack Obama to Congress, addressing the urgent humanitarian situation at the Southwest border of the United States. The letter discusses the rise in apprehensions and processing of children and individuals from Central America crossing into the US through the Rio Grande Valley areas. The President explains that his Administration is taking a unified and coordinated response to address the situation. This includes surging resources to the Southwest border, detaining adults traveling with children, and increasing enforcement efforts. The letter also mentions working with Mexican and Central American partners to address the root causes of migration and improve security. Lastly, the President emphasizes the need for congressional support, including additional legal authorities and emergency supplemental appropriations, to maximize the impact of their efforts.